BENIN  – A professor of Mechanical Engineering, Prof. Vincent Aizebeoje Balogun of the Edo State University, Uzairue, has called on the Federal Govern­ment to create enabling envi­ronment for the green manu­facturing technology sector to thrive in Nigeria through the use of local content technolo­gy for the production of goods in the manufacturing sector. Prof. Balogun made the call in a paper titled, ‘Green Manu­facturing: A Novel Approach to Economic Recovery in Nigeria’, which he delivered at the 3rd Inaugural Lecture series of the Edo State Uni­versity, Uzairue, Etsako West Local Government, Edo State. According to him, Nigeria should capitalise on its pop­ulation of over 200 million people to explore, penetrate and create strong market for its manufacturing sector. Rep Commends Akeredolu’s Commitment To Security In Ondo UAMC Holds 80th Annual Conference “The solution to econom­ic poverty in the country is technological revolution and self-sufficiently in the produc­tion of green consumer goods which can only be achieved through green manufactur­ing,” he said. He pointed out that the only way forward was for the country to take advantage of the green manufacturing strategy and evolve its man­ufacturing sector in that di­rection as the nation move towards the 4th industrial revolution. “The state of manufactur­ing machining in our nation to be specific needs a step change to enhance sustain­ability and transformation towards green,